			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2023</a> paper:</span><br><i>A Low-Code Platform for Systematic Component-Oriented Language Composition</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/JérômePfeiffer.html">Jérôme Pfeiffer</a>, <a href="../profile/AndreasWortmann.html">Andreas Wortmann</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3623476.3623516">10.1145/3623476.3623516</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The main contribution is a low-code platform (tool) that supports systematic component-oriented language composition.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> The platform operationalizes language composition mechanisms by coordinating multiple language constituents (syntax and semantics).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL">T4F: Visualisation</span></a><ul><li> The approach relies on a graphical, web-based interface typical of visualization-oriented tooling.
</li></ul></li></ul>
